35-11 A. STERILIZATION Covered Conditions.--
o Payment may be made only where sterilization is a necessary part of the treatment of an illness or injury, e.g., removal of a uterus because of a tumor, removal of diseased ovaries o Sterilization of a mentally retarded beneficiary is covered if it is a necessary part of the treatment of an illness or injury.
(bilateral oophorectomy), or bilateral orchidectomy in a case of cancer of the prostate.
