Approved Transplant Facilities Intestinal transplantation is covered by Medicare if performed in an approved facility.
The criteria for approval of centers will be based on a volume of 10 intestinal transplants per year with a 1-year actuarial survival of 65 percent using the Kaplan-Meier technique.
More specific criteria can be found at: http://cms.hhs.gov/providers/transplant/default.asp and in the Medicare Intermediary Manual Â§3615.7.
